# Prototype build stamps

When you change the CPFSI prototype (`index.html`, `v1/`, or `v2/`), update `BUILD_STAMPS` in the **root** `index.html` before finishing so deploys are easy to verify.

## Format

UK style: `D Mon YYYY, HH:MM` (24-hour), e.g. `4 Jun 2026, 20:24`.

## Which keys to bump

- **`v2`** — any edit under `v2/` (main workstream).
- **`v1`** — any edit under `v1/`.

Only V1 and V2 cards show stamps; do not add a chooser-page stamp.

Use the current local date/time when updating (not a placeholder).

## Example

```javascript
const BUILD_STAMPS = {
  v1: '4 Jun 2026, 14:31',
  v2: '4 Jun 2026, 20:24'
};
```

Do not skip this step when the user asks for prototype work or when you push substantive UI/flow changes.
